-- England 43-0 After Bowling Out Pakistan for 72 on First Day of Second Test
-- Bob Bensch
-- 2010-08-06T14:46:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-06/england-43-0-after-bowling-out-pakistan-for-72-on-first-day-of-second-test.html

          
          
             England reached 43-0 at tea fter
bowling out Pakistan for 72 on the opening day of their second
cricket Test.  
 Andrew Struass has scored 24 runs for England and Alastair
Cook has 17 at Edgbaston in Birmingham.  
 James Anderson and Stuart Broad took four wickets each
earlier today after Pakistan won the toss and elected to bat.
Anderson finished 4-20 and Broad was 4-38, while Steven Finn was
2-10 for the host. Umar Amin scored 23 for Pakistan.  
 England leads the four-Test series 1-0 after a 354-run win
at Trent Bridge in Nottingham.  
          
          


  


        